cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper introduces a new family of deep neural network models that use differential equations to parameterize the derivative of the hidden state. This approach is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and control systems (cs.SY). Given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The use of differential equations also suggests cs.SY as a possible sub-category.
